  "body": "Ref https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/51903#issuecomment-327290332.\r\n\r\nThis is an issue for old containerd, but the new one may also have this problem.\r\n\r\nWe recently hit an issue in Kubernetes.\r\n\r\nWe added pids cgroup to docker, and set the limit to 4000. However, we found that the pids cgroup run out of pid very soon.\r\n\r\nWe figured out that each `containerd-shim` has more then 10 threads:\r\n```\r\ndocker-containerd-shim\u2500\u252c\u2500nginx\u2500\u2500\u2500nginx\r\n                \u2514\u250010*[{docker-containerd-shim}]\r\n```\r\n\r\nDo we really need so many threads? Should we configure Golang properly to reduce the thread number.\r\n\r\n/cc @yujuhong @shyamjvs",
